Package com.genesyslab.platform.commons.protocol.runtime

Class ProtocolUnknownMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.genesyslab.platform.commons.protocol.DataObject
      • com.genesyslab.platform.commons.protocol.Message
        • com.genesyslab.platform.commons.protocol.runtime.ProtocolUnknownMessage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ProtocolDescriptionSupport
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ProtocolUnknownMessage.ProtocolUnknownMessageData
    public abstract class ProtocolUnknownMessage
extends Message
    This message will be created if incoming message has unknown MessageId. By default this message contains only description of "Reference Id" attribute. Its other attributes are not handled by protocol "Error" handler and PSDK only writes a record into debug log about them. If you need of delivering these attributes you should make a subscription for specific attributes on a specific message(s).

    Note: Do not use this class directly. It is designed for internal use only. 

     This example of attributes subscription:
   AttributeSubscriptionList asl = new AttributeSubscriptionList();
   asl.addAttribute(1001, "1");
   asl.addAttribute(1001, "2");
   asl.applyToContext(protocol.connectionContext());
 
 If message with id 1001 is received, log-file may contain traces like this:
   'ProtocolUnknownMessage' (1001) attributes:
   2 [Integer] 
   1 [String] 
   ReferenceId [int] = 2
